; CCON audit B7 - does a width shrink DESTROY text, or only hide it?
;
; Run:    Execute S:ccon-b7
; Then:   drag the window NARROWER than the text (well under 100 cols)
; Then:   drag it WIDE again
;
;   FIXED / like stock CON: -> the ruler's ..100 and the marker's
;                              B7-END come back when you grow
;   BROKEN                  -> they stay cut off at the shrunk width,
;                              byte-identical to the shrunk state
;
; Run this under stock CON: too (NewShell CON:) and compare - that is
; the whole point. Ed was the original repro, but Ed REDRAWS ITSELF on
; resize, so an Ed test cannot tell "the console kept the data" apart
; from "the client re-sent it". The Shell does not redraw on resize,
; so whatever comes back here came from the console's own buffer.
;
; The ruler and the marker line are each exactly 100 columns, so the
; column where truncation bit is readable straight off the screen.
Type S:ccon-b7-fill
